<subSubSection id="C3466511FFCBFFF575D1ADAFC410AD3E" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="516" pageId="8" pageNumber="514" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE3369AFFCBFFF575D1ADAFC2B4AC8E" blockId="8.[151,1436,1954,2023]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="516" pageId="8" pageNumber="514">
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCBFFF775D1ADAFC762ABE7" bold="true" box="[151,271,1954,1980]" pageId="8" pageNumber="514">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is characterized by male and female frons and face wide; postgena setae stout; cell dm rather truncate; veins M 
<subScript id="17D834DFFFCBFFF7741DADD4C70EABBC" attach="left" box="[347,355,2009,2023]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="514">1</subScript>
, M 
<subScript id="17D834DFFFCBFFF774CCADD4C7FFABBC" attach="left" box="[394,402,2009,2023]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="514">2</subScript>
and CuA+CuP somewhat evanescent distally. 
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCBFFF776DAADCBC58DABBB" bold="true" box="[924,992,1990,2016]" pageId="8" pageNumber="514">Male.</emphasis>
Tergite 8 (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFCBFFF7711FADCBC2B8ABBA" box="[1113,1237,1990,2017]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,248,1278,1302]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,490,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-133@10.[154,1434,489,1255]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Macrostomus penai Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. Holotype ♂ (A–D). A. Tergite 8, dorsal view; B. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; C. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (E–G). E. Female, apex of abdomen, lateral view; F. Female sternite 8, ventral view; G. Genital fork (all figures after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009))." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921367/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="514">Figs 7A, B</figureCitation>
) somewhat short, sinuous distally; all cercal lobes elongate dorsally (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC9FFF5778CAA9AC54CACEA" box="[714,801,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,248,1278,1302]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,490,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-133@10.[154,1434,489,1255]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Macrostomus penai Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. Holotype ♂ (A–D). A. Tergite 8, dorsal view; B. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; C. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (E–G). E. Female, apex of abdomen, lateral view; F. Female sternite 8, ventral view; G. Genital fork (all figures after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009))." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921367/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="516">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
); hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC9FFF5768CAA9AC24CACEA" box="[970,1057,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,248,1278,1302]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,490,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-133@10.[154,1434,489,1255]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Macrostomus penai Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. Holotype ♂ (A–D). A. Tergite 8, dorsal view; B. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; C. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (E–G). E. Female, apex of abdomen, lateral view; F. Female sternite 8, ventral view; G. Genital fork (all figures after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009))." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921367/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="516">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
) somewhat thin, without posterior setae; ejaculatory apodeme without dorsal lamella (
<figureCitation id="13672A1FFFC9FFF57791AAB6C55CAC8E" box="[727,817,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="10.[151,248,1278,1302]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,490,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-133@10.[154,1434,489,1255]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 7. Macrostomus penai Rafael &amp; Cumming, 2006. Holotype ♂ (A–D). A. Tergite 8, dorsal view; B. Tergite and sternite 8, lateral view; C. Epandrium and cerci lobes, lateral view; D. Hypandrium and phallus, lateral view. Paratype ♀ (E–G). E. Female, apex of abdomen, lateral view; F. Female sternite 8, ventral view; G. Genital fork (all figures after Rafael &amp; Cumming (2009))." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921367/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="516">Fig. 7D</figureCitation>
); phallus same length of hypandrium.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF236612FFCAFFF675D1AC88C5EAABBA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4921365" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4921365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4921365/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="515" startId="9.[151,250,1669,1693]" targetBox="[237,1346,182,1645]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8BE3369AFFCAFFF675D1AC88C5EAABBA" blockId="9.[151,1437,1669,2017]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF675D1AC88C778AAC6" bold="true" box="[151,277,1669,1693]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D19FFCAFFF6745BAC8BC4D6AAC6" authority="(Bezzi, 1909)" baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[285,699,1669,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Macrostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="515" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbipennis">
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF6745BAC8BC449AAC6" box="[285,548,1669,1693]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">Macrostomus limbipennis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCD4B6BFFCAFFF67772AC88C4D9AAC6" author="Bezzi, M." box="[564,692,1669,1693]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515" pagination="293 - 407" refId="ref16928" refString="Bezzi, M. (1909) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der sudamerikanischen Dipterenfauna auf Grund der Sammelergebnisse einer Reise in Chile, Peru und Bolivia, ausgefuhrt in den Jahren 1902 - 1904 von W. Schnuse. Nova Acta Academiae Caesareae Leopoldino-Carolinae Germanicae Naturae Curiosorum, 91, 293 - 407." type="journal article" year="1909">Bezzi, 1909</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. ♂ 
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF677A7AC88C549AAC6" bold="true" box="[737,804,1669,1693]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">(A–K)</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF67674AC88C529AAC6" bold="true" box="[818,836,1669,1693]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">A</emphasis>
. Habitus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF67171AC88C225AAC6" bold="true" box="[1079,1096,1669,1693]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">B</emphasis>
. Apex of abdomen, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF675D1ACA4C6C4AA9A" bold="true" box="[151,169,1705,1729]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">C</emphasis>
. Tergite 8, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF674E7ACA4C7DEAA9A" bold="true" box="[417,435,1705,1729]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">D</emphasis>
. Epandrium detached, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF67665ACA4C559AA9A" bold="true" box="[803,820,1705,1729]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">E</emphasis>
. Cerci lobes, epandrium detached, left lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF6700FACA4C335AA9A" bold="true" box="[1353,1368,1705,1729]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">F</emphasis>
. Cerci lobes, epandrium detached, left lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF6771DACC0C402AABE" bold="true" box="[603,623,1741,1765]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">G</emphasis>
. Anterior cercus, cercal bridge and subepandrial sclerite, anterior view; 
<emphasis id="B928EA88FFCAFFF67004ACC0C33BAABE" bold="true" box="[1346,1366,1741,1765]" pageId="9" pageNumber="515">H</emphasis>
